The Senator representing Kaduna North Senatorial District in the National Assembly, Suleiman Abdu Kwari has berated the contractors handling the rehabilitation of Zaria/Pembegua road project. In a statement made available to journalists, he called on the federal government to revoke their license because of their unnecessary delays and shoddiness. He expressed dissatisfaction over the slow pace of execution and the poor quality of work done so far. He said “I have received several complaints from my constituents on the slow pace of the project awarded since 23rd October, 2017 with a 34 months completion period.” “It is obvious the contractor lacks the capacity to handle the project. We owe it a responsibility to ensure that projects meet required standards for the benefit of our people”. 